# Why?

Decompose.  Factor.  Envision simpler problems ... then solve those.

> ... and so I wrote this shell program, and it's 54 lines ... including 
> comments.
>
> *-- William Baxter*

We solve problems with elegance and concision. We factor complex problems into
their simple parts.  

Surely there exists an un-simple problem, we've just yet to meet it.

# What is Simple? 

Readibility is simple.

Clarity is simple.

Comments are simple.

Usage strings are simple.

Brevity.
